0is%20a%20multi-pronged%20attack%20on%20the%20institutions%20that%20have%20stood%20up%20to%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%26quot%3B%20Brescia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20didn't%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deals%20Trump%20made%20with%20Paul%20Weiss%20and%20Skadden%20Arps%20have%20a%20major%20problem%2C%20Brescia%20said.%20Unlike%20a%20judge-approved%20settlement%20agreement%2C%20they%20have%20no%20binding%20power.%20If%20Trump%20is%20unsatisfied%20with%20the%20law%20firms%20at%20any%20time%2C%20he%20could%20impose%20another%20executive%20order%20targeting%20them.%20The%20law%20firms%20can%20only%20feel%20secure%20so%20long%20as%20they%20are%20in%20Trump's%20good%20graces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20a%20Sword%20of%20Damocles%20hanging%20over%20their%20heads%20if%20they%20take%20on%20a%20client%20or%20make%20an%20argument%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20or%20Department%20of%20Justice%20doesn't%20like%2C%20Brescia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClients%20who%20face%20criminal%20cases%20or%20regulatory%20oversight%20may%20not%20believe%20they're%20getting%20the%20best%20representation%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20client%20wants%20a%20lawyer%20who's%20going%20to%20be%20afraid%20of%20the%20government%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-law-executive-orders-disarm-legal-opponents-pro-bono-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743585721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec144a69253ccddf9ae39a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-big-law-executive-orders-disarm-legal-opponents-pro-bono-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Big%20Law%20firms%20often%20lend%20expensive%20legal%20firepower%20to%20civil%20liberties%20organizations%20suing%20the%20govern