sinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-a-hedge-fund-job-point72-academy-applicants-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-competitive%20analyst%20training%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20this%20tech-focused%20version%20is%20a%20continuation%20of%20that%20development%20initiative.%20Gaysinskiy%20said%20he's%20eager%20to%20inject%20the%20firm%20with%20the%20energy%20typical%20of%20younger%20talent%2C%20their%20fresh%20skills%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-programming-languages-work-wall-street-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprogramming%20languages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20engineering%20practices%2C%20and%20data%20science%20fundamentals%2C%20and%20for%20the%20opportunity%20to%20mold%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSetting%20a%20culture%20where%20engineers%20have%20the%20freedom%20to%20innovate%2C%20express%20their%20creativity%20toward%20the%20common%20purpose%20of%20building%20amazing%20solutions%20is%20super%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaysinskiy%20is%20surveying%20the%20firm's%20tech%20population%20to%20get%20their%20input%20on%20their%20desired%20tooling%20and%20apps%2C%20how%20existing%20software%20development%20processes%20could%20be%20improved%2C%20and%20the%20environments%20they%20work%20in%2C%20such%20as%20the%20public%20cloud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20question%20asked%20respondents%20to%2C%20given%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20money%2C%20allocate%20budget%20dollars%20to%20what%20they%20thought%20was%20important.%20He%20plans%20to%20do%20it%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20is%20we%20want%20to%20actually%20start%20a%20systematic%20program%20where%20we%20actually%20are%20very%20data-driven%20around%20what%20needs%20improvement%2C%20what's%20working%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Gaysinskiy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c89a800-a7cc-4a3d-8eca-18369fa346c7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20and%20the%20developer%20experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hedge%20fund%20is%20after%20more%20than%20just%20budding%20technologists.%20One%20of%20Gaysinskiy's%20first%20big%20hires%20was%20Vladimir%20Zhukov%2C%20a%20machine%20learning%20whiz%20who%20will%20run%20the%20firm's%20AI%20and%20data%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20joining%20in%20January%2C%20Zhukov%20led%20various%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning%20efforts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20Stripe%2C%20and%20Amazon%20Web%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAutomation%20will%20be%20a%20key%20part%20of%20Gaysinskiy's%20strategy%2C%20given%20its%20potential%20to%20boost%20worker%20efficiency%2C%20reduce%20errors%2C%20and%20scale%20the%20business%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20automation%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20free%20our%20developers%20to%20focus%20on%20higher-value%2C%20strategic%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaysinskiy%20has%20seen%20firsthand%20the%20power%20of%20AI-assisted%20coding.%20Even%20though%20Gaysinskiy%20considers%20himself%20a%20strong%20coder%2C%20he%20had%20a%20begrudging%20realization%20in%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20that%20%26quot%3BAI%20is%20starting%20to%20get%20better%20at%20this%20than%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20laughing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20realization%20has%20got%20him%20excited%20to%20harness%20the%20power%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20make%20some%20big%20decisions%20on%20where%20to%20concentrate%20the%20firepower%20and%20what%20workflows%20should%20be%20transformed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20advice%20to%20engineers%20working%20in%20or%20planning%20to%20work%20in%20Wall%20Street's%20tech%20ranks%20is%20to%20embrace%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20environment%20is%20constantly%20changing.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20because%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20ripe%20for%20AI%20disruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20much%20of%20the%20business%20is%20digitized%2C%20but%20the%20complexities%20of%20the%20business%20(from%20developing%20software%20for%20different%20financial%20instruments%20to%20the%20regulatory%20nuances%20of%20emerging%20markets)%20has%20largely%20held%20the%20industry%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20engineers%20interested%20in%20applying%20technology%20to%20solve%20interesting%20problems%2C%20and%20particularly%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20the%20AI%20disruption%20will%20occur%2C%20I%20think%20this%20actually%20would%20be%20an%20industry%20to%20watch%2C%26quot%3B%20Gaysinskiy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743584822000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec0320b8b41a9673fc45d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20first%20interview%2C%20Ilya%20Gaysinskiy%20outlines%20his%20tech%20ambitions%20for%20Point72%2C%20from%20AI%20to%20global%20expansion%20and%20culture.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bschan%40businessinsider.com%20(Bianca%20Chan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoint72-cto-ilya-gaysinskiy-tech-talent-ai-plans-hedge-fund-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I've%20negotiated%20up%20to%20%2430%2C000%20more%20than%20I%20was%20offered%20in%20each%20new%20job%20using%20the%20'door-in-the-face'%20technique.%20Here's%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20businessman%20with%20a%20speech%20bubble%20and%20money%20emojis.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dae4f6585f1dff88b295b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETJ%20Patel%20uses%20the%20'door-in-the-face'%20technique%20to%20negotiate%20higher%20salaries%20in%20software%20engineering.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20strategy%20involves%20making%20a%20high%20initial%20request%20and%20then%20a%20more%20reasonable%20follow-up.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPatel%20secured%20offers%20%2410%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000%20above%20initial%20proposals%20using%20this%20method.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20TJ%20Patel%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20software%20engineer%20in%20Austin%20who%20asked%20that%20BI%20not%20name%20his%20employers.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Patel's%20income%20and%20employment%20with%20documentation%3B%20the%20negotiations%20are%20based%20on%20his%20recollection%20of%20conversations%20during%20each%20hiring%20process.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20college%20senior%20when%20I%20learned%20the%20%26quot%3Bdoor-in-the-face%26quot%3B%20technique%20from%20Robert%20Cialdini's%20book%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftakeaways-from-books-about-human-behavior-published-in-2016-2016-12%23-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInfluence%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20used%20the%20strategy%20when%20I%20started%20applying%20for%20jobs%2C%20and%20it's%20helped%20me%20secure%20higher%20salaries%20in%20each%20job%20negotiation%20throughout%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20but%20this%20strategy%20could%20work%20for%20any%20industry.%20You%20only%20need%20data%20on%20typical%20salaries%20for%20a%20specific%20industry%20and%20an%20idea%20of%20the%20specific%20company's%20salary%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20a%20man%20in%20a%20white%20and%20navy%20outfit%20in%20front%20of%20a%20door%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ec2af4b8b41a9673fc4f9d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETJ%20Patel.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20TJ%20Patel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7069953-0780-4d8a-90b9-6882b8b04af1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20technique%20is%20simple%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoor%20in%20the%20face%26quot%3B%20is%20when%20someone%20asks%20for%20something%20big%20or%20unreasonable%20in%20an%20initial%20request%20and%20then%20follows%20up%20with%20what%20they%20actually%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20leverage%20%26quot%3Bdoor%20in%20the%20face%26quot%3B%20after%20reading%20Cialdini's%20example%20about%20organizers%20asking%20for%20donations%2C%20where%20they%20start%20by%20asking%20for%20something%20quite%20large%2C%20which%20is%20almost%20certain%20to%20be%20turned%20down%20%E2%80%94%20the%20door%20slamming%20in%20your%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20they%20pivot%20to%20the%20smaller%20%E2%80%94%20and%20truly%20desired%20%E2%80%94%20ask%2C%20which%20suddenly%20seems%20more%20reasonable%20by%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a104f752-a134-4b02-9519-3f45291119ef%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat's%20when%20it%20clicked%20for%20me%3A%20I%20could%20use%20this%20same%20principle%20in%20salary%20negotiations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bdoor-in-the-face%26quot%3B%20strategy%20has%20a%20real%20risk%3A%20If%20you%20ask%20for%20too%20much%2C%20an%20employer%20might%20decide%20to%20walk%20away%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20if%20I%20was%20willing%20to%20accept%20that%20possibility%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20I%20asked%20respectfully%20and%20backed%20up%20my%20request%20with%20evidence%20like%20competing%20offers%20or%20my%20past%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20then%20most%20reasonable%20employers%20would%20at%20least%20counter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20logic%20was%20that%20if%20they're%20already%20at%20the%20point%20of%20wanting%20to%20hire%20me%2C%20they've%20invested%20time%20and%20resources%20into