ding%20to%20Forbes.%20About%20three-quarters%20of%20these%20women%20inherited%20their%20fortunes%2C%20the%20business%20magazine%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Alice%20Walton%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlice%20Walton%20was%20born%20to%20Walmart%20founder%20Sam%20Walton%20and%20Helen%20Walton%20on%20October%207%2C%201949%2C%20in%20Newport%2C%20Arkansas%2C%20in%20the%20USA.%20She%20completed%20her%20schooling%20at%20Bentonville%20High%20School%20in%201966%20and%20graduated%20with%20a%20BA%20in%20economics%20from%20Trinity%20University%20in%20San%20Antonio%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201974%2C%20she%20married%20a%20renowned%20Louisiana%20investment%20banker%20at%20the%20age%20of%2024%20but%20got%20divorced%20after%20two-and-a-half%20years.%20She%20then%20married%20a%20contractor%20but%20they%2C%20too%2C%20parted%20ways%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20becoming%20the%20head%20of%20investment%20operations%20at%20Arvest%20Bank%20Group%2C%20Ms%20Walton%20worked%20as%20an%20equity%20analyst%20and%20money%20manager%20for%20First%20Commerce%20Corporation.%20She%20worked%20as%20a%20broker%20for%20EF%20Hutton%20as%20well.%20In%201988%2C%20Ms%20Walton%20established%20the%20investment%20bank%20Llama%20Company%2C%20where%20she%20served%20as%20its%20president%2C%20chair%2C%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer.%20It%20was%20closed%20after%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Northwest%20Arkansas%20Regional%20Airport%20and%20was%20the%20first%20person%20to%20chair%20the%20Northwest%20Arkansas%20Council.%20As%20the%20new%20airport%20required%20%24109%20million%2C%20Ms%20Walton%20personally%20gave%20%2415%20million%2C%20and%20her%20company%2C%20Llama%20Company%2C%20helped%20raise%20%2479.5%20million%20through%20bonds.%20The%20main%20terminal%20of%20the%20airport%20has%20been%20named%20after%20her%20to%20honour%20her%20efforts.%20It's%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BAlice%20L.%20Walton%20Terminal%20Building.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20has%20never%20actively%20participated%20in%20Walmart's%20operation%2C%20instead%20preferring%20to%20concentrate%20on%20her%20own%20business%20endeavours%20and%20eventually%20becoming%20a%20patron%20of%20art.%20She%20spends%20her%20wealth%20on%20everything%20from%20horse%20breeding%20to%20pricey%20artwork.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20was%2010%20years%20old%2C%20Walton%20paid%20%242%20for%20her%20first%20piece%20of%20art.%20It%20was%20a%20replica%20of%20a%20painting%20by%20Picasso.%20She%20even%20established%20a%20%2450%20million%20museum%20in%202011%20called%20the%20Crystal%20Bridges%20Museum%20of%20American%20Art%20in%20Bentonville%2C%20Arkansas%2C%20to%20house%20her%20art%20collection%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20valued%20at%20over%20%24500%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Forbes%20report%2C%20she%20has%20also%20previously%20contributed%20to%20Republican%20candidates%20and%20political%20action%20committees.%20In%202016%2C%20though%2C%20she%20gave%20%24353%2C400%20to%20the%20Hillary%20Victory%20Fund%2C%20a%20joint%20fundraising%20group%20that%20supports%20Clinton%20and%20other%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743583980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fjm9mjma8_alice-walton_625x300_27_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fforbes-billionaire-list-2025-who-is-alice-walton-worlds-richest-woman-with-102-billion-fortune-8068236%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20a%20%24102%20billion%20fortune%2C%20Walmart%20heir%20Alice%20Walton%20is%20the%20richest%20woman%20on%20the%20Forbes%20Billionaire%20List%202025.%20Ms%20Walton%2C%2075%2C%20overtook%20French%20L'Oreal%20heiress%20Francoise%20Bettencourt%20Meyers%2C%20who%20held%20the%20title%20last%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fforbes-billionaire-list-2025-who-is-alic