20levels.%20It%20especially%20poses%20a%20worry%20for%20India%20as%20Moscow%20is%20one%20of%20New%20Delhi's%20biggest%20crude%20oil%20suppliers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20crude%20oil%20imports%20crossed%205%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20(bpd)%20in%20March%202025%2C%20the%20highest%20monthly%20volume%20in%20over%2015%20years%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20commodity%20market%20analytics%20firm%20Kpler.%20If%20this%2C%20around%2030%20percent%20of%20it%20is%20imported%20from%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Crude%20Oil%20Imports%20In%20March%202025%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E(Source%3A%20Kpler%20data)%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERussia%3A%201%2C864%20thousand%20bpd%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIraq%3A%20920%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESaudi%20Arabia%3A%20565%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUAE%3A%20424%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUS%3A%20289%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENigeria%3A%20222%20%C2%A0thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKuwait%3A%20110%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAngola%3A%20150%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBrazil%3A%2091%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEcuador%3A%2065%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EColumbia%3A%2063%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVenezuela%3A%2061%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECongo%3A%2058%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EQatar%3A%2036%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGhana%3A%2034%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOman%3A%2033%20thousand%20bpd%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Dependency%20On%20Russian%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20after%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20India%20has%20reduced%20its%20reliance%20on%20Middle%20Eastern%20and%20African%20oil%20in%20favor%20of%20a%20cheaper%20and%20abundant%20supply%20from%20Moscow.%20Refiners%20have%20enjoyed%20bigger%20profits%20due%20to%20the%20cheaper%20supplies.%20In%20fact%2C%20New%20Delhi's%20crude%20oil%20import%20from%20Moscow%20reached%20an%20eight-month%20high%20in%20March%2C%20despite%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russian%20oil%20entities%20by%20the%20outgoing%20Biden%20administration%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kpler%20data%2C%20India's%20import%20of%20Russian%20crude%20jumped%20to%20around%201.9%20million%20barrels%20per%20day%20(bpd)%20in%20March%20-%20marking%20an%20increase%20of%20480%20thousand%20bpd%20month-on-month%20and%20300%20thousand%20bpd%20year-on-year.%20In%20February%2C%20India%20imported%201.47%20million%20barrels%20of%20crude%20oil%20from%20Russia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Threat%20And%20Oil%20Prices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20remark%20pushed%20benchmark%20futures%20up%2C%20with%20West%20Texas%20Intermediate%20surging%203.1%20per%20cent%20on%20Monday%2C%20the%20biggest%20gain%20in%20almost%2011%20weeks.%20Prices%20slipped%20a%20bit%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20but%20steadied%20in%20thin%20trading%20on%20Wednesday.%20Brent%20futures%20were%20unchanged%20at%20%2474.49%20a%20barrel%20after%20slipping%200.4%20per%20cent%20on%20Tuesday.%20US%20West%20Texas%20Intermediate%20crude%20futures%20rose%203%20cents%20to%20%2471.23%20after%20dropping%200.4%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Happens%20If%20the%20US%20Goes%20Ahead%20With%20Its%20Threat%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica%20is%20India's%20top%20trading%20partner%2C%20so%20under%20a%20scenario%20of%20%26quot%3Bsecondary%20tariffs%26quot%3B%20for%20buyers%20of%20Russian%20oil%2C%20India's%20oil%20supply%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20adversely%20affected%20and%20New%20Delhi%20may%20have%20to%20look%20for%20alternative%20supplies%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20Bloomberg.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditional%20sanctions%20have%20created%20enough%20uncertainty%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20quoted%20Warren%20Patterson%2C%20the%20head%20of%20commodities%20strategy%20for%20ING%20Groep%20NV%20in%20Singapore%2C%20as%20saying.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20secondary%20tariffs%20only%20intensifies%20this%20uncertainty%2C%20given%20that%20it%20is%20a%20new%20tool.%20Buyers%20need%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20advantages%20of%20picking%20up%20discounted%20crude%20outweigh%20the%20potential%20hit%20on%20its%20economy%20from%20additional%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Trump's%20threat%20looming%2C%20Indian%20refiners%20have%20rushed%20to%20the%20market%20to%20seek%20crude%20supply.%20The%20Bloomberg%20report%20said%20state-owned%20Bharat%20Petroleum%20Corp%20and%20Hindustan%20Petroleum%20Corp%20are%20seeking%20additional%20supplies%20for%20May%20arrival%20from%20regions%20such%20as%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20North%20Sea%20and%20Mediterranean.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20such%20prompt%20demand%20for%20non-Russian%20cargoes%20likely%20signals%20concerns%20around%20India's%20ability%20to%20receive%20all%20the%20barrels%20refiners%20had%20earlier%20purchased%20from%20Moscow%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Strategy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEager%20to%20keep%20importing%20cheap%20crude%20from%20Russia%2C%20oil%20refiners%20in%20India%20have%20been%20working%20with%20merchants%2C%20shippers%20and%20other%20middlemen%20to%20rebuild%20supply%20chains%20following%20Biden's%20sanctions.%20Last%20month%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%20that%20Indian%20refiners%20were%20reconfiguring%20the%20existing%20networks%20with%20selling%20entities%2C%20tankers%20and%20insurance%20providers%20that%20are%20not%20on%20Washington's%20blacklist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20also%20actively%20diversifying%20its%20crude%20sources%20by%20increasing%20imports%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20Angola%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20West%20African%20to%20reduce%20dependency%20on%20Russian%20oil.%20While%20New%20Delhi's%20import%20of%20Russian%20barrels%20increased%2C%20Indian%20refiners%20also%20imported%20two-thirds%20more%20US%20crude%20in%20March%20than%20in%20February.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20imported%20289%2C000%20barrels%20per%20day%20of%20US%20crude%20in%20March%2C%20up%20from%20146%2C000%20bpd%20in%20February%2C%20according%20to%20Kpler%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20believe%20that%20India's%20strategy%20of%20diversifying%20its%20oil%20supplies%20may%20help%20protect%20against%20any%20impact.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20question%20is%2C%20will%20these%20repeated%20shocks%20end%20up%20structurally%20reducing%20Indian%20appetite%20for%20Russian%20crude%3F%20I%20have%20my%20doubts%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20economics%20works%2C%26quot%3B%20Vandana%20Hari%2C%20founder%20of%20Vanda%20Insights%20in%20Singapore%2C%20told%20Bloomberg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20bluff%2C%20a%20bargaining%20ploy%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Trump.%20But%20refiners%20need%20to%20prepare%2C%20they%20can't%20rely%20on%20hunches%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20bizarre%20and%20unlikely%20a%20supply%20threat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743581640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F9t16r88o_russia-oil-reuters_625x300_02_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-threatens-more-tariffs-on-russian-oil-how-will-it-impact-indias-supply-8068171%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20indicated%20potential%20complications%20for%20Russian%20oil%20trade%20unless%20Moscow%20reaches%20an%20agreement%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-threatens-more-tariffs-on-russian-oil-how-will-it-impact-indias-supply-8068171%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Trump%20%26amp%3B%20The%20Ayatollah%3A%20It's%20a%20Pity%20Both%20Can't%20Lose%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhoever%20said%20history%20repeats%20itself%20was%20not%20talking%20about%20Trump%202.0%20and%20Iran.%20In%202018%2C%20during%20his%20previous%20term%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20unilaterally%20withdrew%20from%20the%20Joint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(JCPOA)%20meant%20to%20restrain%20Iran%20from%20developing%20atomic%20weapons%2C%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20worst%20possible%20deal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20imposed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20policy%20that%20led%20to%20an%2081%25%20contraction%20in%20Iran's%20crude%20oil%20exports%2C%20its%20economic%20lifeline.%20He%20authorised%20the%20assassination%20of%20an%20Iranian%20general%20in%20Baghdad%20in%20early%202020.%20Last%20year%2C%20during%20Trump's%20re-election%20campaign%2C%20an%20alleged%20Iranian%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20him%20was%20uncovered.%20On%20February%205%2C%20soon%20after%20re-entering%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Trump%20restored%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20policy%20against%20Iran.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20US%20intensified%20consultations%20with%20Israeli%20leadership%20to%20prevent%20Iran's%20nuclearisation.%20Why%2C%20then%2C%20exactly%20a%20month%20later%20on%20March%205%2C%20President%20Trump%20wrote%20to%20Iranian%20Supreme%20Leader%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%20proclaiming%20that%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20hurt%20Iran%20and%20its%20great%20people%20and%20suggested%20bilateral%20dialogue%20to%20resolve%20the%20nuclear%20issue%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Deception%20Of%20Public%20Opinion'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20reaction%20to%20this%20Trump%20initiative%20was%20equally%20fork-tongued.%20Even%20before%20he%20had%20read%20Trump's%20letter%2C%20the%20Iranian%20Supreme%20Leader%20publicly%20spurned%20the%20offer%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeception%20of%20public%20opinion%E2%80%9D.%20He%20pointedly%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20know%20they%20won't%20honour%20it%2C%20what's%20the%20point%20of%20negotiating%3F%E2%80%9D%20Three%20weeks%20of%20Iranian%20fire-eating%20rhetoric%20against%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Israel%20followed.%20But%20then%2C%20on%20March%2027%2C%20an%20adviser%20to%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%20said%20that%20Tehran%20%E2%80%9Chas%20not%20closed%20all%20doors%20to%20resolve%20its%20disputes%20with%20the%20United%20States%20and%20is%20ready%20for%20indirect%20negotiations%20with%20Washington.%E2%80%9D%20Iranian%20Foreign%20Minister%20amplified%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20policy%20is%20still%20to%20not%20engage%20in%20direct%20negotiations%20while%20under%20%E2%80%98maximum%20pressure'%20and%20military%20threats%2C%20however%2C%20as%20it%20was%20the%20case%20in%20the%20past%2C%20indirect%20negotiations%20can%20continue.%26quot%3B%20Adding%20another%20twist%20to%20the%20tail%2C%20while%20President%20Trump's%20letter%20was%20delivered%20by%20a%20UAE%20official%2C%20an%20Iranian%20response%20was%20conveyed%20via%20Oman%2C%20which%20hosted%20such%20indirect%20US-Iran%20talks%20during%20Biden's%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20exactly%20is%20going%20on%20amidst%20this%20shadowboxing%2C%20and%20what%20is%20the%20likely%20endgame%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Little%20History%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Iran%20was%20never%20colonised%20by%20the%20West%2C%20it%20was%20often%20subject%20to%20political%20coercion%20aimed%20at%20economic%20exploitation%2C%20particularly%20by%20the%20Anglo-Persian%20oil%20company%20founded%20in%201908.%20In%201951%2C%20Iran's%20populist%20Prime%20Minister%20Mohammad%20Mossadegh%20and%20the%20Iranian%20parliament%20nationalised%20the%20company%2C%20prompting%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%20to%20covertly%20arrange%20a%20successful%20coup%20against%20the%20elected%20government.%20They%20strengthened%20the%20Shah%2C%20a%20megalomaniac%20autocrat%2C%20who%20acted%20largely%20as%20a%20Western%20vassal%20and%20the%20US-appointed%20%E2%80%9CPoliceman%20of%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%E2%80%9D.%20However%2C%20in%20early%201979%2C%20a%20protracted%20popular%20uprising%20deposed%20him%20and%20brought%20in%20Ayatollah%20Khomeini%2C%20a%20Shia%20clergyman%20and%20fierce%20critic%20of%20Shah%20and%20his%20Western%20backers.%20The%20fledgling%20Islamic%20Republic%20of%20Iran%20(IRI)%2C%20a%20theocratic%20democracy%2C%20was%20born%20and%20tapped%20into%20Iranians'%20adherence%20to%20Shia%20Islam%20and%20anti-Western%20sentiments%20to%20gain%20strength.%20The%20IRI%20survived%20a%20bloody%20eight-year-long%20war%20with%20Iraq%20that%20began%20in%201980%2C%20various%20internal%20dissensions%20and%20insurgencies%2C%20serious%20geo-political%20turbulences%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20particularly%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20unmitigated%20Western%20eco-political%20sanctions%20and%20attempts%20to%20isolate%20the%20country%20and%20demonise%20its%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Choking%20Of%20The%20JCPOA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20Tehran's%20nuclear%20technology%20programme%20has%20been%20a%20recurring%20and%20growing%20source%20of%20tensions%20with%20the%20West%20and%20the%20regional%20powers.%20They%20believe%20that%20Iran%2C%20blessed%20with%20huge%20deposits%20of%20hydrocarbons%2C%20does%20not%20need%20an%20extensive%20and%20expensive%20nuclear%20programme.%20It%20is%20widely%20suspected%20to%20be%20a%20Trojan%20Horse%20to%20acquire%20nuclear%20weapon%20capability.%20Although%20Iran%2C%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Nuclear%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%2C%20has%20always%20denied%20such%20ambitions%2C%20it%20has%20also%20asserted%20its%20right%20to%20nuclear%20technology%20for%20peaceful%20purposes.%20After%20extensive%20negotiations%2C%20seven%20global%20powers%2C%20including%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20Iran%20agreed%20in%202015%20on%20a%20JCPOA%20that%20put%20in%20place%20strict%20restrictions%2C%20including%20an%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%20inspection%20regime%20on%20the%20Iranian%20nuclear%20programme%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20the%20uranium%20enrichment%20cycle%20in%20particular.%20In%20return%2C%20many%20of%20the%20Western%20economic%20sanctions%20on%20Iran%20were%20lifted.%20However%2C%20Trump%201.0's%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20JCPOA%20in%202018%20upended%20the%20arrangement%20and%20provided%20Iran%20with%20the%20justification%20to%20enrich%20uranium%20beyond%20the%20stipulated%2020%25%20limit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20the%20Iranian%20acquisition%20of%20substantive%20missile%20and%20drone%20capabilities%20has%20also%20raised%20eyebrows.%20Its%20robust%20support%20to%20some%20regional%20regimes%20and%20non-state%20actors%2C%20such%20as%20Hamas%2C%20Hezbollah%20and%20Houthis%E2%80%94collectively%20dubbed%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CAxis%20of%20Resistance%E2%80%9D%E2%80%94has%20inflamed%20tensions%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%2C%20which%20last%20month%20jointly%20reiterated%20their%20determination%20to%20disallow%20Iran%20to%20acquire%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20capability.%20Israel%2C%20widely%20believed%20to%20have%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20calls%20the%20Iranian%20nuclear%20programme%20%E2%80%9Can%20existential%20threat%E2%80%9D.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20antagonism%20between%20Jewish%20and%20Persian%20civilisations%20dates%20back%20at%20least%20to%20587%20BCE%2C%20when%20the%20first%20Jewish%20temple%20was%20destroyed%20by%20the%20Babylonian%20army%20under%20King%20Nebuchadnezzar%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuspicion%20Above%20All%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20short%20but%20extensive%20background%20puts%20in%20broad%20relief%20the%20long%20mutual%20suspicion%20arrayed%20against%20any%20successful%20resolution%20of%20Iran-US-Israel%20hostility.%20However%2C%20the%20issue%20is%20as%20broad%20as%20it%20is%20long.%20Iran%20is%20already%20a%20formidably%20potent%20foe%20that%20has%20both%20battle-hardened%2C%20technologically%20competent%20and%20ideologically%20motivated%20military%20capability%20and%20a%20siege%20economy.%20If%20it%20further%20acquires%20deliverable%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20it%20would%20become%20virtually%20invincible.%20In%20such%20an%20eventuality%2C%20Tehran%20would%20upend%20the%20longstanding%20Pax%20Americana%20in%20the%20Gulf%20and%20could%20configure%20the%20regional%20geostrategic%20stability%20that%20currently%20favours%20US-Israeli%20preponderance.%20Consequently%2C%20both%20Trump%20and%20Netanyahu%20are%20determined%20to%20prevent%20such%20a%20scenario%20from%20coming%20to%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20any%20objective%20SWOT%20analysis%20would%20show%20that%20Iranian%20nuclear%20assets%20are%20geographically%20diversified%20and%20well-defended%E2%80%94often%20physically%20located%20deep%20underground.%20Tehran%20has%20openly%20warned%20that%20any%20attack%20on%20its%20nuclear%20facilities%20would%20attract%20a%20swift%20and%20disproportionate%20response%20against%20the%20US-Israeli%20interests%20in%20the%20region.%20Further%2C%20such%20an%20act%20is%20likely%20to%20unsettle%20the%20crucial%20global%20oil%20and%20gas%20market.%20While%20the%20Muslim%20Ummah%20is%20not%20quite%20fond%20of%20Iran%20and%20its%20aggressive%20policies%2C%20no%20Muslim%20country%20would%20publicly%20approve%20of%20Iran%20being%20attacked%20in%20this%20manner.%20The%20country's%20regional%20neighbours%2C%20many%20with%20pro-Iran%20Shia%20minorities%2C%20would%20be%20particularly%20wary%20of%20the%20resultant%20instability.%20Although%20the%20clergy-led%20government%20is%20brittle%20and%20unpopular%2C%20a%20foreign%20invasion%20is%20likely%20to%20provide%20a%20much-needed%20rallying%20cry%20for%20its%20support%20base.%20Israel's%20right-wing%20government%20has%20its%20reasons%20for%20not%20only%20supporting%20any%20US%20military%20action%20against%20Iran%20but%20also%20participating%20in%20it%2C%20but%20Iranian%20retaliation%20could%20be%20even%20bigger%20and%20more%20vicious%20than%20seen%20last%20year.%20Moreover%2C%20a%20surgical%20destruction%20of%20nuclear%20capabilities%20would%20not%20be%20enough%2C%20the%20invaders%20may%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20are%20not%20revived.%20This%20may%20necessitate%20a%20regime%20change%2C%20and%20the%20past%20US%20experiences%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20viz.%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20are%20dissuasive.%20Hence%2C%20a%20military%20campaign%20against%20Iran's%20nuclear%20assets%20may%20not%20be%20the%20preferred%20option.%20It%20can%2C%20at%20best%2C%20be%20a%20Pyrrhic%20victory%20without%20any%20guarantee%20of%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20Economy%20Be%20The%20Decider%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran's%20Achilles%20Heel%20is%20its%20economy%2C%20long%20hobbled%20by%20Western%20sanctions%20and%20drained%20by%20the%20heavy%20unproductive%20outgo%20on%20subsidies%2C%20defence%20and%20nuclear%20portfolios%2C%20and%20burdened%20with%20the%20need%20to%20support%20the%20regional%20proxies%20and%20allies.%20While%20Iran%20has%20a%20diversified%20economy%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20exports%20are%20still%20its%20mainstay.%20The%20Western%20economic%20sanctions%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20the%20American%20%E2%80%9Cmaximum%20pressure%E2%80%9D%20campaign%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20seriously%20dented%20it.%20Although%20the%20sanctions%20caused%20serious%20socio-economic%20problems%2C%20such%20as%20public%20disaffection%20due%20to%20high%20inflation%20(40%25%3B%20national%20currency%20has%20lost%2090%25%20of%20its%20value%20since%202018)%2C%20youth%20unemployment%20(22.7%25)%2C%20etc.%2C%20the%20regime%20stayed%20on%20course%20with%20its%20nuclear%20policy.%20During%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20however%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20been%20shaken%20as%20its%20regional%20proxies%20(in%20Gaza%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20Syria%20and%20Yemen)%20suffered%20serious%20setbacks.%20Further%2C%20Israeli%20air%20attacks%20and%20covert%20operations%20against%20Iran%20have%20exposed%20the%20latter's%20vulnerabilities.%20The%20regime%20has%2C%20nevertheless%2C%20sought%20to%20exude%20strength.%20It%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20if%20by%20agreeing%20to%20the%20indirect%20negotiations%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20Iran%20is%20indicating%20a%20higher%20degree%20of%20flexibility.%20Tehran's%20counter-offer%20may%20simply%20be%20a%20ploy%20to%20buy%20more%20time.%20For%20Trump%2C%20too%2C%20the%20negotiations%20offer%20a%20low-cost%20option%3A%20an%20agitprop%20strategy%20to%20divide%20the%20Iranian%20leadership.%20Last%20month%2C%20Russia%2C%20too%2C%20offered%20to%20mediate%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%3B%20but%20the%20recent%20turbulence%20in%20the%20Kremlin's%20relations%20with%20the%20White%20House%20over%20the%20Ukrainian%20conflict%20ceasefire%20might%20have%20put%20that%20offer%20in%20some%20doubt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20low%20mutual%20credibility%20and%20long%20list%20of%20grievances%2C%20the%20proposed%20negotiations%20have%20a%20fairly%20small%20chance%20of%20success.%20Similar%20talks%20were%20held%20in%20Oman%20during%20Biden's%20presidency%2C%20and%20they%20failed%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue.%20A%20parallel%20can%20be%20drawn%20with%20three%20well-publicised%20summits%20Trump%20held%20with%20North%20Korean%20leader%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20that%20failed%20to%20denuclearise%20Pyongyang.%20Further%2C%20the%20motives%20of%20the%20two%20sides%20may%20not%20coalesce%3A%20For%20Trump%2C%20a%20successful%20conclusion%20would%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20require%20a%20deal%20tighter%20and%20more%20intrusive%20than%20the%20JCPOA.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Iranian%20leadership%20would%20perhaps%20be%20happy%20to%20buy%20more%20time%2C%20thwart%20the%20threat%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20and%20negotiate%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20sanctions%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20Easy%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20negotiations%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20protracted%20and%20complex.%20In%20case%20a%20breakthrough%20nuclear%20deal%20is%20reached%2C%20the%20possibility%20of%20more%20ambitious%20workover%20straddling%20various%20geopolitical%20and%20economic%20issues%20in%20suspended%20animation%20for%20nearly%20five%20decades%2C%20such%20as%20softening%20of%20Iranian%20anti-US%20and%20anti-Israel%20profile%2C%20faster%20removal%20of%20sanctions%2C%20return%20of%20frozen%20Iranian%20assets%20as%20well%20as%20leveraging%20Iran's%20economic%20opportunities%20for%20hydrocarbons%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20etc.%2C%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%20Such%20a%20comprehensive%20US-Iran%20makeover%20would%20have%20profound%20implications%20for%20the%20region%20as%20well%20as%20the%20global%20oil%20and%20gas%20ecosystem.%20Some%20details%20are%20likely%20to%20emerge%20by%20the%20time%20Trump%20pays%20his%20first%20foreign%20visit%20in%20his%20second%20term%20next%20month%20to%20three%20Gulf%20countries%2C%20viz.%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20UAE%20and%20Qatar.%20The%20timeline%20for%20proposed%20indirect%20negotiations%20would%20have%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20lapse%20of%20the%20JCPOA%20architecture%20in%20October%202025%2C%20after%20which%20the%20%E2%80%9CSnapback%E2%80%9D%20of%20some%20other%20sanctions%20on%20Iran%20may%20be%20invoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20different%20level%2C%20it%20would%20be%20fascinating%20to%20watch%20the%20forthcoming%20indirect%20and%20secret%20US-Iranian%20negotiations.%20After%20all%2C%20who%20can%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20tryst%20between%20a%20self-styled%20%E2%80%9Ctransactional%E2%80%9D%20deal-maker%20and%20those%20who%20coined%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CBazaar%E2%80%9D%20and%20raised%20negotiations%20to%20the%20art%20of%20%3Cem%3EMutazayedat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20overbidding.%20As%20Henry%20Kissinger%20put%20it%20pithily%2C%20albeit%20in%20a%20different%20context%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit's%20a%20pity%20both%20sides%20can't%20lose%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20Ambassador%20and%20a%20specialist%20on%20the%20Middle%20East.%20He%20currently%20heads%20Eco-Diplomacy%20and%20Strategies%2C%20a%20Delhi-based%20consultancy.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743581460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F25geq3f_iran_625x300_02_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrump-the-ayatollah-its-a-pity-both-cant-lose-8067975%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Who%20can%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20tryst%20between%20a%20self-styled%20%26quot%3Btransactional%26quot%3B%20deal-maker%20and%20those%20who%20coined%20the%20word%20%26quot%3BBazaar%26quot%3B%20and%20raised%20negotiations%20to%20the%20art%20of%20'Mutazayedat'%2C%20or%20overbidding%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrump-the-ayatollah-its-a-pity-both-cant-lose-8067975%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Despite%20the%20Judgment%2C%20This%20Mom%20Focuses%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98Small%20Wins%E2%80%99%20in%20Raising%20Her%20Autistic%20Son%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20Mugdha%20Kalra%20walked%20into%20a%20school%20admission%20interview%20in%202013%20with%20her%20four-and-a-half-year-old%20son%2C%20she%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20a%20routine%20conversation%20about%20his%20future.%20Instead%2C%20she%20walked%20out%20in%20silence%20%E2%80%94%20shaken%2C%20confused%2C%20and%20barely%20able%20to%20drive%20herself%20back%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20day%2C%20a%20counsellor%20gently%20suggested%20something%20she%20had%20never%20considered%20before%3A%20that%20her%20son%2C%20Madhav%2C%20might%20be%20autistic.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20not%20ready%20for%20it%2C%